reviewText: Not what I thought, to dark
Very bloody very gross and really good a great action movie with people kicking a lot of ass just watch the movie

If you want to go on an unpredictable, entertaining and over the top ride....then you will like this film.
If your looking for a thoughtful, moving and profound story....go rent "Seabiscuit".
This film is senseless, over the top grind house and for those who enjoy this kind of fun.
Glad they forced me to rent it. Otherwise would have enjoyed cutting my toenails more.

The film opens in the kitchen of the Long Pig preparing finger food. It includes a nude woman being dragged across the floor. The Long Pig is a specialty restaurant the serves human food, with the dickie wrap being the specialty. One of the characters is named Phat P-h-u-k, eat your heart out Austin Powers.

The entertainment includes nude women dancing in the lobby, sex, and watching combat. The customers get to bid on the parts of the loser. The local martial art gym is being farmed for entertainment until they decide to turn things around.

This is a cult grindhouse. It has the music, nudity, and violence. There was plenty of fighting, unfortunately much of it was dark and fast motion. They needed to develop the gladiator fighting better.

F-bomb, sex, and nudity (Alyson Bath, Natasha Langmann, Aleisha Langmann) Cat fight, fake looking male organ (detached) blood squirting
I enjoyed it.. Remined me of the old-school fighting movies that I grew up with. Fight scenes could of been a little better, but I still enjoyed it..
